#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.131"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.131:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.131:0.2"
msgid "14. Rājavagga "
msgstr "14. Kings "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.131:0.3"
msgid "131. Paṭhamacakkānuvattanasutta "
msgstr "131. Wielding Power (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.148, sc1
#. VAR: vatteti → pavatteti (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.131:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rājā cakkavattī dhammeneva cakkaṃ vatteti; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, possessing five factors a wheel-turning monarch wields power only in a principled manner. "

#. VAR: appaṭivattiyaṃ → appativattiyaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.131:1.2"
msgid "taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ kenaci manussabhūtena paccatthikena pāṇinā. "
msgstr "And this power cannot be undermined by any human enemy. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.131:2.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.131:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī atthaññū ca hoti, dhammaññū ca, mattaññū ca, kālaññū ca, parisaññū ca. "
msgstr "A wheel-turning monarch knows what is right, knows principle, knows moderation, knows the right time, and knows the assembly. "

msgctxt "an5.131:2.3"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rājā cakkavattī dhammeneva cakkaṃ pavatteti; "
msgstr "A wheel-turning monarch who possesses these five factors wields power only in a principled manner. "

msgctxt "an5.131:2.4"
msgid "taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ kenaci manussabhūtena paccatthikena pāṇinā. "
msgstr "And this power cannot be undermined by any human enemy. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.131:3.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammeneva anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavatteti; "
msgstr "In the same way, possessing five factors a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha rolls forth the supreme Wheel of Dhamma only in a principled manner. "

msgctxt "an5.131:3.2"
msgid "taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "And that wheel cannot be rolled back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.131:4.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.131:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho atthaññū, dhammaññū, mattaññū, kālaññū, parisaññū. "
msgstr "A Realized One knows what is right, knows principle, knows moderation, knows the right time, and knows the assembly. "

msgctxt "an5.131:4.3"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammeneva anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavatteti; "
msgstr "Possessing these five factors a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha rolls forth the supreme Wheel of Dhamma only in a principled manner. "

msgctxt "an5.131:4.4"
msgid "taṃ hoti dhammacakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "And that wheel cannot be rolled back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.131:4.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

